news.title: ASPHL upraises Rohit Arora to vice president- North and Goa operations and head of leisure sales, ET HospitalityWorld
news.description: With an exemplary experience of over three decades, his expertise lies in administration management, sales and marketing, relationship building, and operations in the hospitality industry.
news.body: Apeejay Surrendra Park Hotels Limited (ASPHL), a pioneer in the hospitality business with expertise spanning over five decades of owning and operating hotels, has recently elevated Rohit Arora to the esteemed position of Vice President - North and Goa operations and head of leisure sales. He has been associated with ASPHL since 1988 and previously held the position of Area General Manager at THE Park New Delhi.As a visionary and market strategist with a holistic and exceptional skillset, Arora has proven to be an integral asset for Apeejay Surrendra Park Hotels Limited. During his tenure, he has spearheaded THE Park New Delhi in becoming one of the most successful five-star hotels in the heart of the capital of India. In addition to this, he has also successfully launched two premium hotels in Goa under ASPHL. With an exemplary experience of over three decades, his expertise lies in administration management, sales and marketing, relationship building, and operations in the hospitality industry.Throughout his career, Arora has been honoured with several feats for his outstanding work in the industry. He was recognised as the ‘Best general manager’ at India Hospitality Awards - North and East in 2016. Under his leadership, THE Park New Delhi won many accolades, including India’s Best Business Hotel by Travel+Leisure, The Golden Key Award by Nearbuy, Travellers’ Choice Award by TripAdvisor, Corona Warrior of the Year, etc. Arora was recently awarded for his exceptional contribution to the hospitality industry at the Times Business Awards.
